# Linux-side U-Boot env access for fw_setenv / fw_printenv
# Offsets and sizes MUST match linxdot.fragment CONFIG_ENV_* values.
# Linux sees eMMC as mmcblk1 on LD1001 (U-Boot's mmc 0); mmcblk0 is the SD slot.
# Two entries here + CONFIG_SYS_REDUNDAND_ENVIRONMENT in the fragment = redundant
# writes: libubootenv updates the older copy, so a power-loss during saveenv
# still leaves one valid copy.
#
# Device         Offset       Size
/dev/mmcblk1     0xE00000     0x10000
/dev/mmcblk1     0xE10000     0x10000
